Area 13 - Missouri FFA
April 22 at 10:53 PM ·

Zach Evans was recently named the State Forage Production Proficiency winner. Zach is from Richland, Missouri where he works on his family farm of both cattle and forage operations. Zach started his SAE three years ago thanks to his father who was the one that got him started with forage crops. He said "although it is a challenging SAE, it is also a very good learning tool which will help me succeed in the future. Much like many SAE’s, mine forces you to face tough challenges, and you have to learn how to overcome these challenges." Congratulations Zach!

•People must remain 6 feet apart
•If you are sick, stay home

Missouri FFA Association
September 4, 2019 at 3:36 PM ·

FFA members from across the state came together to pack meals to fight childhood food insecurity in the state of Missouri on August 13, 2019 at Food Insecurity Day at the Missouri State Fair. Here are some of the highlights!

Thank you to all of our sponsors who made everything possible:

Presenting: Bayer, Missouri Farmers Care, Brownfield Ag News

Gold: American Family Insurance, MFA Inc., Missouri Farm Bureau, Missouri Farm Bureau Insurance

Silver: FCS Financial, Missouri Corn, Missouri Soybeans, Missouri State Fair, Missouri FFA, National FFA Living to Serve Grant, Missouri Department of Agriculture,

Bronze: NutraBlend, CountryVet, Protect the Harvest,

Packing: A Better Way to Farm, Missouri Rural Electric Cooperative, Missouri Pork, Tyson, Missouri State Fair Foundation, Sydenstricker

Others: Missouri Cattlemen's Beef House, Missouri Pork Place

... and to everyone who made Food Insecurity Day a success-THANK YOU!

Visit mofarmerscare.com for more information about how you can make a difference.

We will have church services today! The second round of winter weather was not as bad as we thought and most of the roads are in good condition. Some outer roads may still have a little snow, so use your best judgment this morning as you consider attending church. The parking lot has been cleared and the sidewalks have been treated. We are ready!

We will be hosting the FFA youth from Richland High School in our worship service this morning. Be sure to welcome them and their families - many will be coming to our building for the first time.

post_text:
#FFA10GallonChallenge

Dairy farmers have been faced with a period of exceptionally low milk prices while the cost of their inputs has remaind the same or increased. This period has caused many dairy farms to sell their cows and farms that have been in their families for generations.

The 10 Gallon Challenge is simple. There is a surplus of milk on the shelves which is driving prices down. The challenge is to purchase 10 gallons of milk from a local grocery store and donate to a local food pantry. Our donation is benefitting our local Good Samaritan.

We are directly challenging the following FFA groups (but encourage everyone to join the challenge):

Stoutland-FFA
Willow Springs Ffa
Crocker Ag Ed
Waynesville FFA
Couch FFA

Lets make this go viral and spread to FFA chapters across the nation to support dairy farmers and our local communities

#10gallonchallenge
National FFA Organization
National FFA Officer Team
Missouri FFA Association
